  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Mount Seir is not the well-known range of Edom. The name ( \"shaggy mountain\") is applicable to any rugged or well-wooded hill. Here it probably denotes the range which runs southwestward from Kirjath-jearim to the Wady Surar. Mount Jearim, i. e. \"woody mountain,\" is through its other name, Chesalon, identified with the modern \"Kesla\".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Beth-shemesh - i. e. \"house of the sun,\" called \"Ir-shemesh\" or \"city of the sun\" (Joshua 19:41; Compare 1 Kings 4:9), a place assigned to Dan, and one of the cities which fell by lot to the Levites Joshua 21:16. Beth-shemesh was the first place at which the ark rested after its return from the hands of the Philistines 1 Samuel 6:12. It was the residence of one of Solomon's purveyors 1 Kings 4:9, and was the spot where at a later date Amaziah was defeated and slain by Jehoash (2 Kings 14:11 ff). It is no doubt the modern \"Ain Shems\".",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Beth-shemesh - i. e. \"house of the sun,\" called \"Ir-shemesh\" or \"city of the sun\" (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Joshua 19:41",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; Compare ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Kings 4:9",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "), a place assigned to Dan, and one of the cities which fell by lot to the Levites ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Joshua 21:16",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". Beth-shemesh was the first place at which the ark rested after its return from the hands of the Philistines ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Samuel 6:12",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". It was the residence of one of Solomon's purveyors ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Kings 4:9",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", and was the spot where at a later date Amaziah was defeated and slain by Jehoash (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Kings 14:11",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ff). It is no doubt the modern \"Ain Shems\".",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Timnah, called also Timnath, and Timnathah, belonged likewise to Dan, and is to be distinguished from other places of like name Genesis 38:12; Joshua 24:30. Timnah ( \"portion\") was evidently, like Gilgal, Ramah, Kirjath, and several other towns, of frequent use in Canaanite topography. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Timnah, called also Timnath, and Timnathah, belonged likewise to Dan, and is to be distinguished from other places of like name ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Genesis 38:12",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
